  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "DL-based classification modelThe proposed 3D Attention-gated Network (3D AG-Net) classification model was adopted from the 2D Attention-Gated Sononet [25].",
    "The 3D AG-Net consists of 17 3D convolution layers (3 × 3 × 3 convolution) to extract features from volumetric CT images input.",
    "Two soft attention gates, AG-1 and AG-2, were placed at the 11th and 14th layers, respectively (Fig. 2).",
    "Deviating from the main network flow, AG-1 and AG-2 can intercept salient features they deem necessary and filter out those features at their specific depths to make independent predictions.",
    "The attention maps generated by the AGs provide visualizations of the network behavior as well."
  ],
